public class CommonElements {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] array1 = {1, 3, 4, 6, 7, 9};
        int[] array2 = {1, 2, 4, 5, 9, 10};

        System.out.print("Common elements: ");
        for (int i = 0; i < array1.length; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < array2.length; j++) {
                if (array1[i] == array2[j]) { 
                    System.out.print(array1[i] + " ");
                    break; // Stops inner loop when a common element is found
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

This program iterates through both arrays comparing each element of the first array with all elements of the second array. When a common element is found, it's printed to the console. The `break` statement optimizes the process by stopping the inner loop once a common element is identified.
